original_title: Sri Lanka beat Ireland, qualify for Super Six
original_body_lines: Sri Lanka qualified for the Super Six stage of the ICC World Cup 2023, beating Ireland by 132 runs in Bulawayo today, on the back of Wanindu Hasaranga's third successive five-wicket haul.
Scotland and Oman also progressed to the next round with Sri Lanka's win.
Chasing a 326-run target, Hasaranga took 5 for 79 with Mahessh Theekshana taking 2 for 28.
Curtis Campher top scored with 39 off 31, with Harry Tector making 33 fron 35 balls.
